<taxonomicName id="33A4D0F8FFC8FFF4E6FCAC34FDD6FCF3" authority="Enderlein, 1936" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1936" box="[247,592,832,860]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Holoneurini">
<emphasis id="C6D07769FFC8FFF4E6FCAC34FE16FCF5" bold="true" box="[247,400,832,858]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Holoneurini</emphasis>
Enderlein, 1936
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BCBEF8F0FFC8FFF4E6E9ACF5FB08FBF3" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F41BAB7BFFC8FFF4E6E9ACF5FB08FBF3" blockId="1.[173,1232,897,1436]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
The tribe is characterized by synapomorphies characteristic of the valid tribe rank in 
<taxonomicName id="33A4D0F8FFC8FFF4E297ACF5FEB8FC13" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Porricondylinae">Porricondylinae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9035D68AFFC8FFF4E747ACD5FE7FFC13" author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[332,505,929,956]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref4430" refString="Mamaev, B. M. 2001. The tribe Holoneurini in the Palearctic (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). All-Russian Institute of Continuous Education in Forestry, Pushkino, 17, 1 - 11 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="2001">Mamaev, 2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="9035D68AFFC8FFF4E40FACD5FCBDFC13" author="Fedotova, Z. A. &amp; Sidorenko, V. S." box="[516,827,929,956]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="235 - 277" refId="ref4217" refString="Fedotova, Z. A., Sidorenko, V. S. 2007. New taxa of gall midges (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae, Porricondylinae) with reduced wing venation and flagellomeres from Russia. An International Journal of Dipterological Research, 18 (4), 235 - 277." type="journal article" year="2007">Fedotova, Sidorenko, 2007</bibRefCitation>
): antennae with 10–11 flagellomeres; reduction of wing venation; absent or reduced parameres; tarsal claws narrow and curved near midlength; male and female flagellomeres with dense sensorial reticulation, and female flagellomeres with a long neck. Their wing venation is variable, with 
<emphasis id="C6D07769FFC8FFF4E5BDAB75FC5EFB8D" box="[950,984,1025,1058]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
M 
<subScript id="6820A93EFFC8FFF4E5DBAB60FC5EFB8D" attach="left" box="[976,984,1044,1058]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">3</subScript>
</emphasis>
absent or slightly visible, 
<emphasis id="C6D07769FFC8FFF4E6E8AB55FE83FB94" box="[227,261,1057,1083]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Cu</emphasis>
never forked, 
<emphasis id="C6D07769FFC8FFF4E7A2AB55FE63FBED" box="[425,485,1057,1090]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
CuA 
<subScript id="6820A93EFFC8FFF4E7D6AB40FE63FBED" attach="left" box="[477,485,1076,1090]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
slightly visible distally or completely disappearing, 
<emphasis id="C6D07769FFC8FFF4E224AB55FBFEFB95" box="[1071,1144,1057,1082]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">m+rm</emphasis>
usually slightly curved distally, and 
<emphasis id="C6D07769FFC8FFF4E7E7AB35FD86FBF5" box="[492,512,1089,1114]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">rs</emphasis>
situated at an angle to 
<emphasis id="C6D07769FFC8FFF4E50CAB35FC9EFBF5" box="[775,792,1089,1114]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">R</emphasis>
<subScript id="6820A93EFFC8FFF4E513AB27FCA6FBCE" attach="left" box="[792,800,1107,1121]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">5</subScript>
. The ovipositor is 2-segmented.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BCBEF8F0FFC8FFF4E6E9AB15FE35FA33" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F41BAB7BFFC8FFF4E6E9AB15FC8EFB13" blockId="1.[173,1232,897,1436]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
The larvae of some extant species of the 
<taxonomicName id="33A4D0F8FFC8FFF4E4C0AB15FCD8FBD3" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1936" box="[715,862,1121,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Holoneurini">Holoneurini</taxonomicName>
have been associated with leaf litter and decaying wood (
<bibRefCitation id="9035D68AFFC8FFF4E7EBABF5FCA9FB33" author="Mamaev, B. M. &amp; Krivosheina, N. P." box="[480,815,1153,1180]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 278" refId="ref4470" refString="Mamaev, B. M., Krivosheina, N. P. 1965. Larvae of gall midges (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Comparative morphology, Biology and keys. Nauka, Moskow, 1 - 278 [In Russian]." type="book chapter" year="1965">Mamaev, Krivosheina, 1965</bibRefCitation>
). Adult insects are usually captured in Malaise traps (
<bibRefCitation id="9035D68AFFC8FFF4E77DABD5FD32FB13" author="Fedotova, Z. A. &amp; Sidorenko, V. S." box="[374,692,1185,1212]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="89 - 127" refId="ref4166" refString="Fedotova, Z. A., Sidorenko, V. S. 2005. New species of gall midges of the subfamily Porricondylinae from the Russian Far East (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). An International Journal of Dipterological Research, 16 (2), 89 - 127." type="journal article" year="2005">Fedotova, Sidorenko, 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 2007).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F41BAB7BFFC8FFF4E6E9ABB5FE35FA33" blockId="1.[173,1232,897,1436]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
The tribe includes 12 genera and 43 species: 9 extant genera with 38 species (number of species in parentheses): 
<taxonomicName id="33A4D0F8FFC8FFF4E41DAB95FCD6FB53" authority="Mamaev, 1960" authorityName="Mamaev" authorityYear="1960" box="[534,848,1249,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Cassidoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C6D07769FFC8FFF4E41DAB95FD1AFB54" box="[534,668,1249,1275]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Cassidoides</emphasis>
Mamaev, 1960
</taxonomicName>
(8); 
<taxonomicName id="33A4D0F8FFC8FFF4E583AB95FB19FB53" authority="Meijere, 1901" authorityName="Meijere" authorityYear="1901" box="[904,1183,1249,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Coccopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C6D07769FFC8FFF4E583AB95FC71FB54" box="[904,1015,1249,1275]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Coccopsis</emphasis>
Meijere, 1901
</taxonomicName>
(8); 
<taxonomicName id="33A4D0F8FFC8FFF4E6A6AA75FD2FFAB3" authority="Fedotova et Sidorenko, 2005" authorityName="Fedotova et Sidorenko" authorityYear="2005" box="[173,681,1281,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Cognitepidosis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C6D07769FFC8FFF4E6A6AA75FED3FAB4" box="[173,341,1281,1307]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Cognitepidosis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="9035D68AFFC8FFF4E757AA75FD2FFAB3" author="Fedotova, Z. A. &amp; Sidorenko, V. S." box="[348,681,1281,1308]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="89 - 127" refId="ref4166" refString="Fedotova, Z. A., Sidorenko, V. S. 2005. New species of gall midges of the subfamily Porricondylinae from the Russian Far East (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). An International Journal of Dipterological Research, 16 (2), 89 - 127." type="journal article" year="2005">Fedotova et Sidorenko, 2005</bibRefCitation>
